Text.string: Dee looks angry!
Where the hell is everybody?
Where'd you bastards run off to?
Rogues, come in. Do you copy?
Archimedes, you there?
Now, I hid some loot nearby. Go on, give the Rogue-Sight a whirl. Just look through the scope.
Someone got the drop on my Rogues and took the fragment, but I ain't no detective. Good thing I've got somethin' pretty damn close. Hit that button over there.
Let's start with Agent Dee. He's the closest.
Make contact with Dee while I alert the others on a secure line and tell 'em you're comin'.
Agent Dee is master of disguise. And traps. And a helluva pole dancer, hah! Which is more useful in this galaxy than you might think. You'll see.

Agent Dee's been running a honey pot. He's got them COV hypnotized. Until you signal Dee to break cover, those bandits won't lift a finger. Figures. Those dumb bandits fell for Tyreen 'cause no one else here loved 'em, or looked at 'em. But that ain't a reason to burn down the galaxy.
What a relief. Agent Dee's alive and up to his tricks.
Ooooh-wee. Whole lotta COV. I'm guessing Agent Dee probably left some traps nearby in case the honey pot went sour. Might as well arm 'em. Use the Rogue-Sight.
When you're ready to break Dee's cover, shoot that mark with the Rogue-Sight.
(looping salacious cheers, a la bachelor party)
Like I said, the Rogues were running counter-ops against the COV while looking for the fragment. With that Rogue-Sight, you can track 'em down.

See, from time to time a smuggler needs to drop his cargo in a hurry, so the Rogues use a special loot tracker. Designed it myself! With that baby, we can hunt down lost cargo across the entire planet. But in this case, we're gonna track down that fragment AND the traitor who stole it.
This thing we're doing, going after the Great Vault, serving two Siren streamers on their quest to become gods? This is your life's work. 'Cause you'll all probably die in the process!

Think about that, everyone. Yes, it's true that you COULD be learning valuable lessons like how to grow your own crops, or how to read, but whatever. Kill innocent civilians—that's how you show the galaxy you are special, that you matter! Am I right?
Better to be prepared than dead. Yup, that sounds like wisdom.
That one could come in handy.
Yup.
(disappointed heckles)

Those dropships come in day in and day out. See, those cultists are runnin' an organ traffickin' ring, slicin' up poor SOBs and sellin' their parts all across the galaxy. So, I set up a ship scanner so I can track the shipments.
Show's over, fellas!
Die, you dumb bastards!
Let's get these inbred chode chokers.
You with Clay? Good, let's kill!
Watch my ass! Time to squash these turd teasers!
Nice fighting. Got some loot in a chest over there. On top of the generator in the corner. Just use the Rogue-Sight to find it.
Now, let me, uh, slip into something more comfortable.
Clay says there's a traitor among us, and you need my ID. All yours, baby.
Whoever the traitor is, Clay's gonna tear him limb from limb—if I don't find him first.
Well, time to head to the docks and find my buddy Domino. Best sharpshooter in the Edens, and polite as pie. It's his thing. Hope Domino's alive—not many Rogues left.
The COV has the Ambermire on lockdown, but my crew built a secret entrance in. Use the Rogue-Sight to find it.
Nice killin'!
Watch out! Dropship incomin'! Please find some cover, Vault Hunter!
Head's up! Mad bombers! I'll try to pick a few of 'em off, if that's all right with you.
Nailed 'em!
You see that?
Got one!
Ship's comin' in. Find some cover!
Damn, ship's takin' off. Don't worry, we'll grab the next one.
Secret entrance should be close. Remember to use your Rogue-Sight's scope to find it.
Wouldn't ya know it? That ship scanner's broken. You're gonna have to climb that crane to fix the darn thing and get it into position. Then I can track the ship. Appreciate it.
Now get to that scanner. Thanks a bundle!
Ughh, must've jammed. Kick it or somethin'. Thanks again. I hate these sickos, and you're a real help.
Another ship! Fend 'em off while the scanner warms up!
Wow, did you see that? Didn't plan that blast, but I'll take it! Let the dominoes fall where they may!
All done! By the way, my ID's stashed in my “office”. Clay says you're hunting down a traitor. Good luck! I'm gonna stick around and shoot COV. It's a livin'. Nice meeting ya!
Still can't believe one of my Rogues went rogue, but... I guess it's in the name. Language, right? That's on me. My bad.

Clay, hope you're hearin' this. I think one of the Rogues turned COV. I'm goin' undercover to investigate. Find me and we'll share intel. This ECHO log will self-destruct in three seconds. Beep, beep, beep...||Gahahaha! Just kiddin', Clay! I wouldn't kill you. We're family, buddy.

Someone definitely sold out the Rogues, Clay. See, I infiltrated an offshoot of the Reek Water gang called the Mud Necks. Turns out Aurelia Hammerlock offered one of the Rogues the Eden-7 system in exchange for a Key fragment. Don't know who yet. If you don't hear from me, buddy, then assume the worst. I'm either dead or captured. But come find me anyway! I'd do it for you.
Almost done.
That jabber is pissed!
Access denied.
Mmrmm! Mmrgrhr guh nmnrap!
Ugh, thanks. But it's a trap! Get ready to fight!
That's the Mud Neck leader! He's got my intel. Let's kill 'em!
Brutal. What they deserved, though. There's my ID.
Never found the traitor. But I'm guessin' Clay's gon' use the Loot tracker. That's what it's for. Anyway, here's my ID.
That's all the IDs. Nice work, Vault Hunter. Now back to Rogue's Hollow—it's time to activate the loot tracker.
Wow... brutal.
If I had an army of jabbers, I could take over the planet. Just sayin'.
Look at that jabber go!
Aw, damn—that was gruesome!
That animal is a force of nature!
Children of the Vault, baby!

Come on down to the orgy of blood!||Kill some Vault Thieves, make the crimson flood!||I fight for our mighty God-Queen!||The diva of destruction who we call Tyreen.||But don't forget our God-King Troy.||In his blood-soaked name, we destroy!||Oh, won't ya come kill some Vault Thieves with me?||Won't ya kill some Vault Thieves with me, baby?||Give it up for the COV!||The only cult for you and me.||We got guns and guts, bullets and bones.||And our family never fights alone!||Crush the Vault Thieves, grind 'em to sand.||Got fire in my eyes and an axe in my hand.||Won't ya kill some Vault Thieves with me, baby?||Won't ya kill some Vault Thieves with me?
(dying)||Ook!
Get the hell outta here!
Vault Hunter, I am told you have recovered another Vault Key fragment. Please come see me on Sanctuary.
Bring the fragment to my lab.

Vault Hunter! Clay says the operation was a success. Well, I've got good news as well. I know where the third fragment is. It's right under the harpy's snout! We can nab it and open the Vault all in one fell swoop!
That leaves only one more fragment. Once you acquire it, I will join you at the Vault.
Keep shooting those marks, Vault Hunter.

(faux female voice)||That's right! The corporations, they treated you like hot garbage. But you're not trash, you are beautiful. Not face beauty. And you all smell like crap, let's be honest! But that's just part of what makes you special!
Oh, and keep that Rogue-Sight handy. You'll need it to signal my crew to break cover.
All right, we just need one more ID.
Access granted.
The loot tracker!
That's like six times his body weight!
Ook! Ook Oook Ooooook!
Jabber's saying the fragment's just up there. Nice job, little jabber. Do your thing, baby.
All right, Vault Hunter. Let's get that fragment, and find out who betrayed the Rogues.
All right! Next stop, the Ambermire.
We need to make contact with my crew leader, Archimedes. He'll sort this all out.
When I find that traitor, we are gonna have words. Be on your guard—the traitor could be anyone. Even me. But it's not. Maybe it's you. Just kiddin'. We'll get to the bottom of this together.

Archimedes and I used to run smuggling ops against all the corporations. A while back, we tried to steal some firearms from Montgomery Jakobs himself. Archimedes made it out all right, but I got caught. Instead of throwin' me in the Anvil, Wainwright's daddy offered me a job.

You gotta hand it to the Calypso Twins. Wrangling an entire army of devoted followers for free. Bet the corporations wish they'd thought of that, instead of treating the malcontents and air-breathers of the galaxy like yesterday's dead skin. Just sayin'.
Base should be close now. And yup, you guessed it—you can use the Rogue-Sight to find it.
All right! Gettin' closer. Head on in and find Archimedes.
Did that jabber just punch a face off? Nasty!
Gotta be those COV bastards. We'll see what Archimedes has to say. If he's alive, which is... seeming less likely by the minute.
That jabber's cookin' up some murder spaghetti and I'm gonna sauce it up.
Don't like the looks of this, but see if you can make sense of the mess.
Someone threw a blood orgy and everyone was invited.
I've seen this before. Brief, highly-localized hurricane.
This place smells of organic suffering... with a hint of fermented sardine.
Hnh. Reminds me of my first piano recital.
All right. We should check the security console.
Quietfoot's a crazy bastard. We go way back. You've gotta find him, Vault Hunter.
You seein' this?!

Damn. Forgot about that. See, every Rogue has a security ID, like the one you picked up from that bloody mess that WAS my man Archimedes. Looks like whoever killed my Rogues was smart enough to take the rest of their IDs. Good thing I still got a few live agents in the field. You'll need to get their IDs before we can activate the loot tracker.
Ohohohoh! That was a good one!
There you go.
All yours, Vault Hunter.
You put that to good use, yeah?
Don't forget to use your Rogue-Sight, Vault Hunter. Ha, guess you're one of the Rogues, now.
Clay says there's a traitor among us, and you need my ID. All yours, baby.
Whoever the traitor is, Clay's gonna tear him limb from limb—if I don't find him first.
Gotta say. I never thought I'd be using the loot tracker to hunt down a traitor. Maybe Aurelia's right about loyalty. All comes down to a paycheck.
I see you comin', Vault Hunter. Clay said he was workin' with some serious muscle. I'm in a secure location overlookin' a dock full of COV. Need some help clearin' 'em out—we'll talk after, thanks.
Turn back before you get hurt, whoever the hell you are!
Jabber tracker! Damn. Ook-ook in peace, little jabber man.
What the hell? Clay?
Gehehehhh! We'll see about that, Clay. I've got a new family now. And a new shine, thanks to Troy Calypso!
Damn, he's one of those Anointed freaks. Show him what happens to traitors, Vault Hunter!

Smooth operator! Now it's time to track down Quietfoot—hunter by trade, dead drop master. Been settin' up listening devices to gather intel on the COV. Let's check his dead drop and see what he's been up to.
Once you scan those IDs, the loot tracker should lead us straight to the fragment—and the traitor.
All right, now shoot the console. Just kidding. Don't... do that. That's an amazingly expensive piece of tech. Just scan the IDs and activate the loot tracker.
Fragment acquired.
Got the fragment.
I have the fragment.
Got the fragment, boyo.
This is the most sophisticated tracker money can buy. Beats drones, bots, you name it, in every conceivable test. And without further—you know, that fancy word for waiting—here it is!
Take out those COV. Got you covered. Good luck.
Ado! Ah, that's the word. “Without further ado.” Learned that from a guy I killed. Real egghead. Was holding a book and everything.
Ook.
Hell yeah, holographic monkey!
I love it. Does it come in gold?
Exactly as I envisioned.
Holo-jabber. I used one of these for an Anshin job.

Little known smuggler secret. You wanna find something, use a jabber. Fast as hell, got a nose like a bloodhound. We digitized that little bastard so it doesn't crap everywhere. I ain't no turd farmer.
Ook!
Now follow that jabber!

You know, despite being betrayed by one of my own, it feels good to be back in the field, even vicariously. That's a fancy word I learned from that nerd I killed. Helpful guy. Maybe should have chatted him up a little more before I offed him.
Damn, it's dark. See if you can get the lights on.
Quietfoot! Oh, man!
Ook! Ook!

Smooth operator! Glad you're here, 'cause I could use a hand. See, I used to run with a smuggling crew called the Rogues. Well, I called 'em in to find the Key fragment, and they did. Infiltrated the COV and went deep undercover—so deep that now I can't get ahold of those bastards. So, I need you to track 'em down. Here, take this.
That jabber's trying to tell us somethin'!
Quick, find some cover! That traitor used Quietfoot as a trap to kill you!
That Fragment's close, I can feel it in my gut. Could be that saurian tartare I had for lunch, though. That means fancy raw meat, if you was wondering.
Damn it to hell, that traitor's gonna pay! Look around where Quietfoot used to be. His ID should still be there—those things are indestructible. Wish I could say the same for my crew.
Don't look down—it'll only make ya crap yourself.
Stay back! I'm warning ya! I'll put ya in the mud!
See those invisible marks? Shoot to activate!
Welcome to the Ambermire. Back in the day, some Jakobs whose name I don't remember lined the swamp with oil rigs, but now it's just an oily graveyard. Anyway, the Rogue base should be up ahead.
Archimedes? That you? I thought you were dead! Ohhhh. I see—you faked your own death, sold out the Rogues. Helluva manuever—what'd you get for it?
Aurelia promised me two planets and enough cash to build a waterslide between 'em! The dream we always talked about! It's happenin', Clay! It's happenin'! Guhuhuhuhoo!
We call that the Rogue-Sight. Guess what it does.
Proud of you, man. You did it! Vault Hunter... kill that traitorous sumbitch.
Archimedes? Where the hell are you, man?
Grab his security ID, Vault Hunter. We might need it.
Initializing security protocols. Scanning...
Me and Archimedes worked together for years. Sad to say goodbye, but... a traitor's a traitor, even if they were family. Well, you see the fragment?
Ook!
Ook indeed, my brother. Ook indeed.
As I knew you would, Vault Hunter. After all this is done, you should join the Rogues—we could use someone like you.

I should tell you, Aurelia offered me a small fortune to turn against Wainwright and y'all, but I didn't take it. Montgomery Jakobs, he was the closest thing to a father I had. Well, those Calypso Twins murdered him, and Aurelia helped. So when you and Wainwright are ready to make a move, you let me know. And for the record, I ain't in it for the money.
Try out that Rogue-Sight, Vault Hunter. One of my crew's marks is nearby.
I do not guess. I ascertain. It... I don't know.
Makes people's brains explode? Fingers crossed! It's me birthday!
Steals memories? I mean, who would want that? Heh...
Identifies thieves and makes them more punchable. Handy.
Thinking you're nearin' a mark. Give that Rogue-Sight a whirl.
One of my crew must've left something nearby. Look down the Rogue-Sight's scope and you'll find it.
The Rogue-Sight'll show you my crew's invisible marks. Ain't that something?
Vault Thief! Need your help. See, we're victims of our own success. Remember that vid where Troy super-murdered your Siren friend? Well... how do we top it?

I don't know... do we kill some orphans, or... kill some puppies, or cram a bunch of puppies in an orphanage and burn it to the ground? It's a dilemma! What's gonna keep the offerings flowing?||Ooh, Ty! Maybe we let our followers decide.
A murder poll! Love it. Gotta run, super fan. The Great Vault beckons—we'll be gods soon, bitches. Laters!
I've been working for the Jakobs Corporation ever since. Montgomery Jakobs taught me that everyone has a price, and if you want to survive this shitstorm of a galaxy, you'd better know yours.
That ain't Archimedes.
Forget his name, but guess it don't matter now. Ain't gonna put the candy back in that piñata.
Can't believe it. Half the Rogues are dead... Someone is gonna pay for this in blood.
Rogue-Sight can do it all, baby. Leave secret messages, hide loot, mark POIs, lay traps. Every smuggler in the Rogues uses one. And now you've got one.
Me and that fella used to be the pride of the Vastlands. Now he's just cold cuts and guts.
Damn, that's Cassie. Best smuggler in the Rogues. Least, she was.
Looks like you missed one.
Hard to make out the face, but that's Archimedes' ID. Guess he's really gone.
Let's take a look.
Agh, when's Archimedes comin' back?
Said to hunker down. Extraction ain't happening today... maybe tomorrow.
How long does he think we can keep this fragment hidden? Swamp's crawlin' with COV.
Hey, what the hell?!
How'd they find us?!
